"We’re only 6 months in! We are here for the long-run. As a business, we are thinking in terms of “years” and “DECADES,” not in terms of “days” or “weeks”. We’re building a franchise around your Lil’ Heroes and so this is really just the beginning..." - LH Founder

"Our tech team will reveal details about Training Camp in the coming weeks, but I can tell you this: Training Camp will reward those that hold of BOTH Lil’ Heroes and Lil’ Villains with exclusive merch, tickets to IRL events, and even more access to Edgar’s world." -LH founder
"We will be minting Lil’ Villains, the counterparts to Lil’ Heroes later this summer. We’ll be releasing sneak peeks of the art in the coming weeks so keep a lookout for those!" - LH Founder

"A lot has happened in the last 6 months. And a lot is yet to come. Building a lasting brand takes time, and we understand that 6 months is merely a blip on the long life of this project." -LH founder

"As of today, out of 7777 Lil’ Heroes, only 250 are for sale– which is 3.2% percent of the total collection. Which means, we have a lot of Diamond Hand holders excited about where the project is heading." - LH founder

"We had our first IRL event for holders at the SoHo house in NYC. Edgar was there, QuestLove was our headliner, and all attendees received an exclusive print.

Edgar created this exclusively for our community it's and just a taste of what we have in store in terms of merch."

"In terms of partnerships and collaborations, we’ve partnered with numerous celebrities, like J Balvin, DJ Khaled and the Nobel Peace Prize recipient, Maria Ressa. We’ve also partnered with other great Web 3 projects, and are in negotiations with some true titans of this space."

"We are creating a Virtual Writers’ Room, so that you can be a part of the story and the creation of the Lil’ Heroes’ journey.

We can’t wait to harness the power of this community to create something truly spectacular together." - LH Founder

"We have enlisted the former President of Hasbro Studios, Stephen Davis, to advise on the creative direction of the show. Hasbro Studios is responsible for franchises like: Transformers, My Little Pony, GI Joe, so we really have the best-in-the-business bringing our LH to life."
"We’ve teamed up with 10-time NBA All Star @carmeloanthony and his production company, Creative 7, to executive produce our upcoming series and voice one of the Lil’ Heroes characters." = LH Founder
"The goal is to use these incredible characters from Edgar Plans to create an animated series and entertainment franchise, and we continue to charge ahead on that front." - LH founder

"Part of our mission has always been to have a positive impact on the world around us. We’re wholly committed to helping address climate change and ocean conservation. That’s why we teamed up with Project Hiu--we’ve donated $83,000 to their conservation efforts" - LH founder

"Our Roadmap, like most in the space, has evolved and even though we still have a lot to deliver on from our original roadmap, we’ve also done a lot of things in the past six months that weren’t part of the original plan" - LH founder

"It’s almost exactly 6 months since we launched Lil Heroes on January 16th - so it’s the perfect time to review where we’ve been, take stock of where we’re at today, and talk about what the future holds." - LH founder

"I'm trying to give more and more to this community. I think that NFTs are a way to give access to a bigger community--but we are not just focused on NFTs. This is a way to be a part of all the amazing things that Lil' Heroes will do in the future." -@plansartstudio

"How can we get a hold of a Lil' Villain?"

"The easiest way to get a Lil' Villain is to get a Lil' Hero now. You'll be guaranteed a Lil' Villain." - Lil' Heroes founder
"If you have a Lil' Hero, you'll be able to mint a Lil' Villain for free. This is a reward for our community and a chance for more people to come into the Lil' Heroes universe." - Lil' Hero founder

"A lot of collectors who are buying Edgar's physical work are traditional collectors, who resonate with his characters.
They're familiar and also completely his own." - @ChristiesInc

"What's the 'floor price' of some of @plansartstudio physical works?"

"For a large painting, you're looking at six figures in resale."- @ChristiesInc

ALPHA: "Lil' Villains are the key to our Training Camp. Training Camp will be our community's ticket to exclusive merch, signed items, event access, tickets, and some really special things that we have in the works." - Lil' Villains founder
"As we thought about our entertainment franchise, we thought about what we needed…you need a villain so that heroes can do their job!" - Lil' Heroes founder

"We're in talks with a major Hollywood showrunner and then we'll open up a virtual writers' room for the community for the development of the show. We want to bring our community into the process and really be a part of the show." - Lil' Heroes founder

"I emailed Edgar as a fan, telling him I loved his characters and that I wanted to bring them to life in an animated series. The intent was always to build this into an entertainment franchise." -Lil' Heroes founder
"These characters started 10 years ago to represent a philosophy around solidarity, fighting climate change, and everyday super powers that reside in these little animals"- @plansartstudio

- A celebrity musical act

We’re selecting a well known, top Hollywood showrunner to bring this show to life. But we’ve also seen how many talented people this community has, therefore we’re creating an exciting mechanism for people to collaborate in the “Writers’ Room”.

11/14🧵

So far we’ve been lucky to onboard celebrities like @JBalvin, @Iamwill, @MariaRessa, and our very own TV series Executive Producer, @CarmeloAnthony. 

10/14 🧵

9/14 🧵

ALPHA: you’ll need both your Lil’ Hero and Lil’ Villain to advance in the “Training Camp” 👀

8/14 🧵

As we get closer to the upcoming mint, remember that you’ll be able to mint a free Lil’ Villain for every Lil’ Hero that you own.

7/14 🧵

We’re getting closer to the launch of Lil’ Villains! Lil’ Villains are the counterpart to Lil’ Heroes. Some of you might feel closer to one or the other. Lil’ Villains look spectacular and are truly state-of-the-art, and we’re sure you’ll love them instantly.

6/14 🧵

This “Training Camp” is one of the most innovative utility mechanisms in NFTs, and we’re excited to contribute to the web3 space with the infrastructure we’re building.

5/14 🧵

A roadmap with tangible utility for collectors is central. We’re currently building a robust system called “Training Camp” that will give collectors the chance to receive incredible rewards that will make this collection more dynamic, with access to Edgar’s world.
4/14 🧵

This is not just a pfp project but a legacy and sustainable entertainment franchise that includes a TV show, brand collaborations, IRL events, access to Edgar’s art, impact initiatives & so much more.

3/14 🧵

We’re building a long-term project, with arguably one of the most talented artists in the web3 space, @plansartstudio. Once breaking records in auction houses like @ChristiesInc, Edgar Plans is now breaking boundaries in the metaverse.

2/14 🧵

It’s been an intense couple of months at @LilHeroesNFT. We wanted to share a quick recap on what we’ve been building so far, and the things coming ahead 🚀.

OUR GOAL:
Our ultimate goal is to build an entertainment brand with lasting power and different touchpoints with its audience, from NFTs to merchandise, to shows and gaming, to IRL experiences and in the metaverse. That is our vision and ultimate goal.

COMPANION:
We will grow together in the coming months. We are working on our companion collection, which will be airdropped to current holders. We will also find a way to prioritize those that couldn’t mint and offer them a chance to join the Lil Heroes Holder community.

AIRDROPS/PASSIVE INCOME:
We will be partnering with other collections we admire to do WL giveaways as well as NFT and ETH airdrops.  
We’re also looking to offer our community the ability to Stake and earn rewards. We’re working with legal counsel on this.

2) VALUE: Holders will receive access to WL from partner collections, NFTs from our own collection and partners, and ETH airdrops. 
3) PARTICIPATION: Holders will be able to participate in setting the roadmap, the causes we support and the development/production of the TV show.

VALUE:
We want to make sure that holding a Lil Hero is valuable in the short, mid-term and long-term. These are some of the utilities we’re thinking about:
1) ACCESS: Holders will get preference in future collections, ability to purchase Edgar's art, IRL and virtual events.

Q4: We hope to be pitching the series and have a distribution platform and production agreement. By then we will also launch an experience in the metaverse. 

Finally, we will also start holding IRL gatherings for holders.

Q3: We will hire the showrunner for the show and open the virtual ‘Writer’s Room’, where the community can participate in the development of the show. We will also have the tokenization of one of Edgar's works offered exclusively to holders.

Q2: Towards the end of Q1, beginning of Q2 we will launch our Companion Collection. We will offer holders the opportunity to have a physical piece created by Edgar (Look out for more info on this in the coming weeks).

ROADMAP:
Q1: We planned the Mint, partnerships with Sotheby's and Phillips for charity auctions + a unique conservation experience for a member of the community. It will be the first of many partnerships.
